# Context System

## Context Files

Pre-generated context files exist in `output/context/`. Use these INSTEAD of scanning the full codebase:

| File | Purpose |
|------|---------|
| `module-index.md` | Feature map of all frontend/backend modules |
| `sprint-digest.md` | Pre-computed sprint status summary |
| `api-index.md` | All API endpoints by router |
| `schema-digest.md` | Database schema from ORM models |
| `patterns.md` | Canonical code patterns to follow |

Also load `output/project-context.md` for critical implementation rules.

## Regeneration

Context files should be regenerated after significant code changes:

```bash
python scripts/context/generate_all.py          # Regenerate all
python scripts/context/generate_all.py --sprint  # Sprint digest only
python scripts/context/generate_all.py --check   # Check if stale
```

## Configuration

Edit `scripts/context/context-config.yaml` to configure scan paths for your tech stack.
